President Barack Obama issued a statement on Armenian Remembrance Day, recognizing the atrocities committed against Armenians during the final days of the Ottoman Empire in 1915. He expressed his view that 1.5 million Armenians were massacred or marched to their death, and emphasized the importance of acknowledging these historical facts. President Obama also commended the dialogue and reconciliation efforts between Turks and Armenians, as well as the contributions made by Armenians around the world. He concluded by expressing admiration for the Armenian people and their ability to overcome the dark past and inspire hope for the future.